Unchanged Impact to our thesis
In- line Financial results versus consensus
Modest revision higher Direction of next 12- month consensus EPS
Source: Company data, Morgan Stanley Research
NCI reported \(34\%\) earnings growth in 1H, higher than MSe at \(23\%\) , implying annualized ROE up 9ppts to an impressive \(32\%\) . Interim dividend was up \(24\%\) .
Value of new business (VNB) was up a strong \(58\%\) , in line, with growth driven mainly by doubled first- year premium, while VNB margin saw some decline.
Agency force is stable with productivity gain. Banca VNB up \(1.4x\) and accounted for \(53\%\) of VNB. Overall VNB's sensitivity to investment return is declining.
Net asset was down \(13.3\%\) h- h while up \(4.5\%\) q- q. A more stable interest rate could help its net asset improve. CSM balance up a small \(0.7\%\) and EV up \(8.1\%\) h- h.
Overall, the 1H result is strong, while business quality still need further improvement to catch up with peers; H- share valuation is higher among insurers now.

We apply a \(14\%\) discount rate to properly reflect current market volatility and NCI's small- cap profile. We use \(30\%\) , \(59\%\) and \(80\%\) dividend payouts in the three stages of 2025- 27, 2028- 33, and \(>2033\) , respectively, and corresponding dividend growth rates of \(- 14\%\) , \(26\%\) and \(2\%\) . The implied 2025E P/B ratio for NCI is \(1.2x\) in our base case scenario.
